It's a five guys....if you haven't heard of them by now then I'm not really sure what rock you have been hiding under. However if you are looking for fast food burger alternative that does not break the bank and taste pretty good, then this is probably a spot for you.  Burgers are good but tend to be pretty greasy. The selling point here is once you have chosen you burger (single Patty or double) you can basically add any of the toppings (as much of each, but you have to ask them to write it twice. For example double mushrooms) with no additional cost. So get filling.  When it comes to ordering fries they don't cheap out on you. One order is enough for at least 2. Not only do they fill the cup size that you ordered but for good measure they dump a bunch extra into the bag.  And if all that was not enough you can eat your fill of free peanuts whole waiting.  There are some alternatives to the burger available just in case you want to be different.  Don't expect anything special from the staff here but maybe different location will vary.
